maml:description.maml:para: Creates a copy of the specified Power BI report.
Creates a copy of the specified Power BI report in the same Power BI workspace or in a different workspace and rebinds the report to a referenced dataset in the target workspace.

maml:Description.maml:para: The ID of the original report to copy.

Optional parameter for specifying the target associated dataset ID. If empty, the new report will be associated with the same dataset as the source report.

The workspace object, as obtained by using the Get-PowerBIWorkspace cmdlets, where the original report is located. If empty, source workspace is 'My Workspace'.

maml:description.maml:para: Creates a copy of the specified Power BI tile and adds it to a Power BI dashboard.

Creates a copy of the specified tile and adds it to a dashboard. If target report ID and target dataset ID are not specified, the following can occur: * When a tile copy is created within the same workspace, the report and dataset links will be copied from the source tile.
* When copying a tile to a different workspace, the report and dataset links will be rested, and the tile will be broken.

maml:Description.maml:para: The ID of the dashboard where source tile is located.
Optional parameter for specifying the action in case of position conflict. The default is 'Tail'.
The ID of the dashboard where tile copy should be added.
